<h1>{{ title }}</h1>

<p>I'm an expat living in Hong Kong with my wife for some time. I've worked in public relations, ran a graphic design studio, and taught English as a foreign language at several universities, both in the US and China. Not necessarily in that order. </p>

<p> As the title suggests, this site may be the missing chapter of an encyclopedia in a story bby Jorge Luis Borges, or it may just be a place for me to keep track of what I'm reading. No one may ever know for sure. 

<p>What began as a simple way of keeping track of what my small book club (and me on the sly) expanded out into more subjects and then contracted back to leave room for other creative pursuits.  </p>

 <p>The creative brief for this site: I wanted simplicity. Security. Files as app, so I wouldn't be locked into a database. I found 11ty (eleventy) as someone who rarely codes, fit the bill. It just works.   </p>

 <p>If you have any questions, comments, or suggestions, please don't hesitate to reach out to me at davidrosshk@gmail.com.</p>